  "assumptions": [
    "Traffic assumed ~<50k webhooks/mo (moderate volume); all three tiers handle the same load at different robustness levels",
    "Downstream consumers are Lambda functions (extensible to HTTP endpoints via EventBridge API destinations in resilient tier)",
    "Webhook senders use HMAC-SHA256 signatures for payload verification",
    "Fan-out target count assumed 2–5 consumers; SNS topic per event type scales this trivially",
    "No compliance regime flagged; standard security floor applied",
    "Alerting destination assumed email (budget) → Slack (balanced) → PagerDuty (resilient)",
    "Cost estimates are on-demand list prices for us-east-1, presented as ranges over assumed monthly volumes. They exclude the AWS Free Tier, Savings Plans, Reserved Instances, and negotiated discounts.",
